Reasoning: The paper presents a new dataset for advancing the state-of-the-art in small object recognition and scene understanding, which are topics that fall under computer vision (cs.CV). The dataset also includes ground truth for object classification, detection, and semantic segmentation, which are tasks that are commonly addressed in machine learning (cs.LG, cs.AI). The paper also discusses the statistical analysis of the dataset, which involves natural language processing techniques (cs.CL). Finally, the paper provides baseline performances for object classification, which is a task that is relevant to multimedia (cs.MM).
